1.       Open up Android Studio
2.       Choose Configure
3.       SDK Manager
4.       Load
5.       Show Package Details
6.       Many Packages to Install…
a.       Android 5.1.1- Select everything, except for TV and Wear- 4 of those options
b.      Android for 5.0.1
c.       Android 4.2.2- Select everything but glass development kit preview
7.       Go to the second tab
8.       Make sure you have…
a.       Android SDK Build Tools
b.      Android SDK Tools 24.4
c.       SDK Platform Tools
d.      Android Support Repository
e.      Android Support Library
f.        Google Repository
g.       Google USB Driver
9.       Press Apply and follow directions, don’t click cancel
10.   Click okay to go back to the Configure
11.   Press back button to go to Quick Start
12.   Click import project
13.   Go to downloads folder
14.   Open ftcappmaster folder
15.   ftc_app-master- green icon
16.   Click okay
17.   Progress bar 
18.   Open up to a screen with no files
19.   Project, Structure, and Capture
20.   Click on Project
21.   FTC robot controller
22.   Open up Java
23.   Opmodes
24.   For Teleop- K9 Teleop
